## 🏆 Tier 1 — High-Impact Features (Build These First)

These directly solve pain points that cost travel agents hours per itinerary.

---

### 1. ✏️ Inline Itinerary Editing
**Problem:** Agents always need to tweak AI output — swap a restaurant, shift timings, add a client's specific hotel. Right now they must regenerate the entire itinerary or edit the PDF externally.

**Solution:** Make the timeline view editable:
- Click any activity to edit time, description, or delete it
- Drag-and-drop to reorder activities within a day
- Add new activities at any point in the timeline
- Edit daily area focus / title

**Why it matters:** This is the #1 thing that turns "cool AI toy" into "production tool." Agents will adopt this overnight.

---

### 2. 🏨 Hotel & Flight Information Blocks
**Problem:** Itineraries without accommodation and flight details are incomplete. Agents currently add these manually in Word/Canva after downloading the PDF.

**Solution:** Add structured input fields for:
- **Hotels**: Name, address, check-in/check-out, booking ref, star rating per night
- **Flights**: Airline, flight number, departure/arrival times, terminals, PNR

These should appear prominently in the PDF output and the timeline view (at the start/end of each day or as separate header blocks).

**Why it matters:** Eliminates the biggest post-generation editing task. The PDF becomes truly "ready to send."

---

### 3. 👥 Client/Lead Management (CRM Lite)
**Problem:** Agents juggle dozens of client inquiries. They generate itineraries but have no way to tie them to specific clients or track which proposals are pending.

**Solution:**
- Add a `clients` table: name, email, phone, notes, tags
- Link each itinerary to a client
- Client dashboard showing: all proposals sent, status (draft/sent/confirmed/rejected), follow-up dates
- Quick "Duplicate & Customize" — clone an existing itinerary for a new client with minor tweaks

**Why it matters:** This turns GozyTrips from an "itinerary tool" into a "business tool" that agents open daily.

---

### 4. 📧 Direct Email/WhatsApp Share
**Problem:** The current workflow is: Generate → Download PDF → Open email/WhatsApp → Attach → Send. Four steps.

**Solution:**
- **Email**: One-click "Send to Client" button that emails the PDF + a styled HTML preview directly
- **WhatsApp**: Generate a shareable link (public read-only itinerary page) that the agent can send via WhatsApp
- **Tracking**: Optional read-receipt / link-open tracking so agents know if the client viewed the itinerary

**Why it matters:** Reduces the delivery workflow from 4 steps to 1 click. Agents send 10-20 proposals/day — this saves real time.

---

### 5. 📋 Itinerary Templates & Reusable Packages
**Problem:** Agents sell the same Bali 5-night or Rajasthan 7-day packages repeatedly. They regenerate from scratch each time.

**Solution:**
- Allow saving any itinerary as a "Template"
- Template library with search/filter (by destination, duration, budget)
- "Use Template" → pre-fills the form and generates a customized version with the new client's dates
- Option to create templates manually without AI generation

**Why it matters:** For popular routes, this brings itinerary creation time from ~3 minutes to ~30 seconds.

---

## 🥈 Tier 2 — Differentiation Features (Build Next)

These separate you from competitors and create stickiness.

---

### 6. 💰 Costing & Pricing Module
**Problem:** After generating the itinerary, agents manually calculate costs, add markup, and create a pricing breakdown.

**Solution:**
- Per-activity cost fields (entry fees, transport, meals)
- Hotel and flight cost integration
- Auto-calculated trip total with configurable agent markup (% or flat)
- Cost breakdowns in PDF: per-day and total, with/without markup (agent view vs client view)
- Multi-currency support (INR, USD, EUR, etc.)

**Why it matters:** This is the #1 feature request in every travel agent tool survey. It's where agents spend the most time after itinerary creation.

---

### 7. 🖼️ Destination Images in Itinerary
**Problem:** Plain text itineraries don't excite clients. Agents add photos manually in Canva/Word.

**Solution:**
- Auto-fetch destination/attraction images using Unsplash API (you already have `unsplash.ts`)
- Include curated images in the PDF per day or per activity
- Allow agents to upload their own images for specific activities
- Cover photo selection for the itinerary header

**Why it matters:** Visual itineraries convert better. This is a common client complaint — "the itinerary looks boring."

---

### 8. 🗺️ Interactive Map View
**Problem:** Clients (and agents) struggle to visualize the route and proximity of attractions.

**Solution:**
- Embed a map (Google Maps or Mapbox) showing all daily stops as pins
- Route lines connecting each day's activities
- Day-by-day toggle: show only Day 1 pins, Day 2, etc.
- Include a static map snapshot in the PDF export

**Why it matters:** Map view is the #2 most requested feature in B2B travel tools after costing.

---

### 9. 🌐 Multi-Language Itinerary Export
**Problem:** Indian agents serve clients who speak Hindi, Gujarati, Marathi, etc. International agents need itineraries in Arabic, French, etc.

**Solution:**
- Language selector in the form (Hindi, English, Spanish, French, Arabic, etc.)
- AI generates the itinerary directly in the chosen language
- PDF export respects the selected language

**Why it matters:** Opens up non-English-speaking market segments. Very few competitors offer this.

---

### 10. 📊 Agent Dashboard & Analytics
**Problem:** Agents don't know which destinations are popular, how many itineraries they've created this month, or their conversion rates.

**Solution:**
- Dashboard with: itineraries created (by week/month), top destinations, average trip duration, average budget
- If CRM is built: proposal-to-booking conversion rate, revenue tracking
- Export reports for team leads / agency owners

**Why it matters:** Agency owners/managers want visibility. This is what drives enterprise/team adoption.

