## 🥉 Tier 3 — Growth & Moat Features (Long-Term)

These create viral growth and competitive moats.

---

### 11. 🔄 Itinerary Versioning & Comparison
Save revision history. Let agents compare v1 vs v2 side-by-side when iterating with clients.

### 12. 🤝 Team/Agency Accounts
Multiple agents under one agency. Shared template library, shared client database, role-based permissions (admin, agent, viewer).

### 13. 📱 Mobile-Responsive Itinerary Viewer
A public shareable link that renders beautifully on phone screens. Clients rarely open PDFs on mobile — a web-based itinerary viewer with swipeable days wins.

### 14. 🧠 AI "Regenerate Section" 
Instead of regenerating the entire itinerary, let agents select a specific day or time block and say: "Regenerate just Day 3 with more adventure activities" or "Replace the lunch spot with something vegetarian."

### 15. 📅 Seasonal & Event Awareness
AI considers local festivals, weather patterns, peak/off-peak pricing in its recommendations. Show tags like "Cherry Blossom Season 🌸" or "⚠️ Monsoon — pack rain gear."

### 16. 🔗 Booking Integrations
Partner with booking APIs (hotels, flights, activities) so agents can add affiliate links or direct booking buttons. Revenue share model.

### 17. ⭐ Client Feedback Collection
After the trip, send clients a feedback form. Agents build a verified review portfolio to show new prospects.

